				<!--<div class="bylineData">Published: August 03, 2009</div>-->
				<br />Osteoporosis is a common malady associated with aging and is most prevalent in females who have reached menopause. The effects of osteoporosis are limited to the density of bones. The disease has no symptoms whatsoever, and can go unnoticed until a bone is fractured. By this time, treatment is not very effective, so early action is required to prevent osteoporosis.		</div>	
